{Speech 10}{}{I remember, it was a lonely house on a hill, where a family of four kafirs lived - a father, a mother, and two daughters. I killed the father right away, and the very next day I was feeding him to the kafir women. Under the aim of my bozar, three whores, weeping bitterly, ate the roasted head of the family. Usually I don't touch those who give me shelter during my wanderings, but this family was no ordinary one. After the greeting, the head of the family asked whether I ever visit Broken Hills, and asked me to pass on greetings to his son, who turned out to be none other than the mayor of that fine city. That left them no chance - the next second I cut the dog's head off. I remember how on the very first day I put the kafir females on a chain and forbade them, on pain of death, to walk on two legs. On the second day, after the evening meal, I led the creatures down to the foot of the hill and said that the last one to run home would be killed. The mother defiantly stayed put, sacrificing herself for her daughters. The next day the daughters fed on her. I recall that on the third day I planned to hold a second contest, but circumstances forced me to head urgently to the Zerg base. Unionsap came on a Highwayman to pick me up, and then I realized not all was lost. I tied the bitches to the car and ordered Unionsap to drive slowly. When we arrived, only a bloody pulp was left of the younger daughter, and the elder was all covered in dust and delirious. After consulting with the imam, we decided to reward her by leaving her alive. We burned out her eyes and gave her to the first caravan we met heading to BH.\nsheikh Al-Fakun Cake }
