{Speech 19}{}{As a child I was an obedient, kind boy. But then I started gambling at coin-toss, fell in with pirates, and went sliding downhill... The road of blood and mass murder led me to the Zerg. What a time it was... You get up in the morning, brew some strong coffee, grab the good old minigun - and off into the Wasteland. Mountains, mountains of corpses - women, children, animals... So many fun things happened - take, for instance, my bet with the boys over whether we could fire a paladin out of a rocket launcher - the experiment only half succeeded, we loaded him inside and then forgot him there. And then for some reason they shut down "Project Broken Hills"... Or how we assembled power armor out of firewood, lizard hide and the corpses of Klamath Security staff? And we did assemble it, at that. To this day I can't forget how Fargus kept repeating "Godforsaken gopniks... godforsaken gopniks... they kill the pajamas... they kill with pajamas..," even when his head was torn off and fed to the ratpigs. It was a wonderful time. Though there's more yet to come...\nBerserker}
