{Speech 36}{}{Under cover of night I make my way into the inner part of the Shelter-City. My target is the first wing of the retirement home, where war veterans from all over California found their final refuge. I understood that I would hardly manage to leave here alive, but I was glad that it was I who would deal with them. They poisoned the lives of all the wasteland's inhabitants and imposed their own order everywhere. The retirement home is several blocks away, the guards are positioned very precisely, only a professional could pass unnoticed. I creep through the narrow streets between the houses, slip away from the watchmen's sharp eyes, how I want to kill them. But I have to keep moving. A few dozen meters left to the building. 10 meters. 5 meters. At last. I see an open window on the ground floor, I climb in. It's a bathroom. I hear some grunting in stall №3, I understand it's time to act. I drew my knife, with a powerful kick I knock down the door, I pounce on Lamar Simms sitting on the toilet. I plunged the knife into the area of his liver and with effort drew it along his belly. His guts spilled out of his slit-open gut, for a few seconds he still looked at me and his eyes were empty. I stand over his corpse and smile, how I love the sight and smell of a freshly gutted corpse. It gives me strength. I walk along the corridor, entering every ward. How good it is that these feeble old men can't hear the dying screams of their former comrades-in-arms. How I love all of this, rivers of blood, gutted bodies, severed limbs. My mind clouds over and each killing turns out more horrible than the last. I took scalps, peeled the skin off heads. On those still alive, I carved meaningless symbols with my knife. One old man, Max, I simply beat to death. I punched him in the face with my fist, with each blow it looked more and more like just a piece of bloody meat. I realized he was already dead, but I couldn't stop. I wanted to see his brains start to come out of his ears. Only dust remained of his skull bones. "Alright, that's enough now" - I said. I reached for the exit, but then the door suddenly opens and into the room comes a huge black guard, with an assault rifle in his hands. With a precise hook I sat him down on the ground, drew my trusty Glock and put a bullet right between his piggy eyes. Some scurrying started in the corridor, I understood they'd come for me. Picking the assault rifle up off the floor, I opened fire at the source of the sound. Through the holes in the drywall I noticed the guards, catching a bullet, falling in heaps. You get far less of a high from killing like that. Ceasing fire, I felt a strong pain in my chest, lowering my head, I saw blood flowing from a gaping hole, I no longer had the strength to stand, I tried to lean against the wall, it didn't work, my hand treacherously slipped. I lie in a pool of my own blood, I understand this is the end, but I regret nothing. I managed to kill 19 old men. Tomorrow the whole town will be talking about me, and perhaps the whole wasteland.\n\nKotyara}
