{Speech 18}{}{A shot. A dying scream. The spray of their blood on my face. I look up at the sky - and the sun smiles at me. I could do this forever. A shot. A dying scream. His lungs fly outward along with shards of bone. Isn't it beautiful? The moment when, together with the creature you've killed, its entire little world dies - it's for this moment that I live. To destroy. To erase. To kill. Everything else is illusory and doesn't matter. There aren't enough people in the world for me to sate myself on their deaths. To gouge out the eyes. To twist out the collarbones. To rip out the jaw. I used to be sentimental - I killed my beloved girl so as to kiss her, gazing into her fading eyes. To wipe the thin trickle of blood from her forehead, cover her with a blanket and say "Good night." Much time has passed. Everything living in this world exists only thanks to \nthe magnanimity of Super Azein. Enjoy your last moments. The day will come, and I will come for you.\nSUPER AZEIN}
