{Speech 40}{}{Entry - night of 24.07.2241. On this warm July night, Insane's feverish brain spawned yet another diversion. Having finished the cave orgy, we set off to the laboratory. A couple of men started to make a dash for the Patriarch's little room, but I stopped them in time. The old man hadn't yet recovered after a brahmin, stoned out of its mind on a cocktail of jet and buffout, raped him rectally. This, however, didn't stop him from repeating the mantra CROCODILE DICKHEAD CHEESE, even in his sleep.\n}
{Speech 40 Answer 41}{}{Next}
{Speech 41}{}{We picked out of the pen a couple of the toughest-looking slaves, who called themselves Bumpit and Peepeekin. It was amusing to see these little beasts whimpering as they were dragged outside. The look that Peepeekin cast at the sky, brimming with a thirst for freedom, did not escape notice.\n}
{Speech 41 Answer 42}{}{Next}
{Speech 42}{}{The rules were simple. They are free… if they can run away. When they heard this phrase, a spark of hope lit up in their eyes, as if they believed they could actually obtain the freedom they longed for. A light flick of the knife, leaving a palm-length wound on their bellies, quickly brought them back to reality.\nThey ran, clutching their gaping wounds with their hands, trying to keep their innards from sliding out. And meanwhile Cocaine went off to let his pack of wild dogs out of the cage, which hadn't been fed since yesterday…}
{Speech 42 Answer 5}{}{Return to the main menu}
