{Speech 12}{}{Having taken fuel for a hundred jets of napalm, I set off to Redding. According to rumors, another group of cowardly heretics from the alliance was due to arrive there. On the way I came upon a herd of lizards, ate my fill. On the main street there turned out to be about 20 people. Armed heretics and just ragamuffins. I walked on, burning out the heresy. The heresy scattered, stank, fired back and screamed. To this day I remember the smell of burning meat and steel welding itself to the body and the pools of fat from the melting lolodins. And the delightful screams, a balm for the ears. It was a good day.\n\nRecorded by an adept of the religion of the Sleeper, Aoi Re. Glory to the Sleeper and his children, and to those whom he patronizes. The Sleeper and the Zerg.\n}
